thoughts.reasoning_problem:
Context: If people own a large desktop monitor at their home, then they work regularly and often at home. All people who have a fully stocked and impressive home office are people who own a large desktop monitor at their home. All people who work regularly and often at home spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their homes. All people who work regularly and often at home visit the office supply store regularly. If people spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, then they do not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon. Remy either both goes to bed late and wakes up every day after noon and spends their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, or they do not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon nor spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home.
Question: Based on the above information, is the following statement true, false, or uncertain? Remy has a fully stocked and impressive home office and also visits the office supply store regularly.
Options: A) True B) False C) Uncertain
raw_logic_programs:
Predicates:
OwnMonitor(x) ::: x owns a large desktop monitor at their home.
WorkHome(x) ::: x works regularly and often at home.
ImpressiveOffice(x) ::: x has a fully stocked and impressive home office.
Tidy(x) ::: x spends their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home.
VisitStore(x) ::: x visits the office supply store regularly.
LateSleep(x) ::: x goes to bed late and wakes up every day after noon.
Premises:
∀x (OwnMonitor(x) → WorkHome(x)) ::: If people own a large desktop monitor at their home, then they work regularly and often at home.
∀x (ImpressiveOffice(x) → OwnMonitor(x)) ::: All people who have a fully stocked and impressive home office are people who own a large desktop monitor at their home.
∀x (WorkHome(x) → Tidy(x)) ::: All people who work regularly and often at home spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their homes.
∀x (WorkHome(x) → VisitStore(x)) ::: All people who work regularly and often at home visit the office supply store regularly.
∀x (Tidy(x) → ¬LateSleep(x)) ::: If people spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, then they do not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon.
(LateSleep(remy) ∧ Tidy(remy)) ⊕ ¬(LateSleep(remy) ∨ Tidy(remy)) ::: Remy either both goes to bed late and wakes up every day after noon and spends their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home, or they do not go to bed late and wake up every day after noon nor spend their free time tidying and organizing the spaces in their home.
Conclusion:
ImpressiveOffice(remy) ∧ VisitStore(remy) ::: Remy has a fully stocked and impressive home office and also visits the office supply store regularly.
